column4: Quantitative Literacy – QNT1 Express information – Students express information in multiple mathematical forms.
column11: Advanced: Students express information symbolically, graphically, numerically, and verbally, and transition easily from one form to another.
column13: Proficient: Students express information in three of the four forms listed in the Level 4 description and transition easily among those forms.
column15: Progressing: Students express information in two of the four forms listed in the Level 4 description and transition easily between those forms.
column17: Beginning: Students express information in one of the four forms
column19: Unsatisfactory: Students are unable to express information in any of the four forms listed in the Level 4 description.
